      "message": "[Major] Line 179: 🟡 Suggestions - The async closure revalidates that the call still exists, but then applies the stale `callDictionary` captured before dispatch. If the daemon updates the call details/state between the callback and the barrier block, this can overwrite newer data or trigger an incoming notification for a call that is no longer incoming. Re-fetch the details used for the mutation inside the serialized block, or explicitly verify the state is still incoming before notifying.\n```suggestion\nguard let latestCallDictionary \u003d self.callsAdapter.callDetails(withCallId: callId, accountId: accountId) else { return }\n_ \u003d self.callManagementService.addOrUpdateCall(callId: callId,\n                                               callState: .incoming,\n                                               callDictionary: latestCallDictionary,\n                                               mediaList: withMedia,\n                                               notifyIncoming: true)\n```",
